# Unit Testing Standard

Full standard: [docs/agent/standards/testing/unit.md](../../docs/agent/standards/testing/unit.md)
Workflow + templates: `.cursor/skills/testing/SKILL.md`

- Unit specs live in `src/api/test/unit/**` and mirror the `src/` tree (e.g. `src/core/auth/roles.guard.ts` → `test/unit/core/auth/roles.guard.spec.ts`). Do NOT co-locate specs with source.
- Import the unit under test via `@core/*` / `@domains/*` aliases (location-independent). Mock all deps — no real I/O, no real DB, no real Redis.
- Cover four categories per public method: happy path, validation errors, edge cases, error conditions.
- Reset mocks in `afterEach(() => jest.clearAllMocks())`. No shared state between tests.
- Deterministic fixtures via factories in `src/api/test/helpers/factories/` (fixed UUIDs and dates).
- Assert specific error classes (`NotFoundError`, `ConflictError`, etc.) — never test raw error messages.
- Coverage ≥ 90% lines/branches/functions for services.
- Use `jest-mock-extended` for typed mocks of Prisma and injected services.
